dictionary.description: Alza Masta was imprisoned in another world after confronting the Holy Emperor, although only their own powers could rival those of one another. Had the Holy Emperor not had assistance with sealing Alza Masta away, their roles in history would have most likely been reversed. Alza Masta would have probably used the knowledge he would've acquired after defeating the Holy Emperor to guide his rule of Grand Gaia, perhaps stopping the Holy Emperor's plans to destroy humankind altogether. However, there's no doubt that he would've ruled over Grand Gaia with an iron fist, unforgiving of the slightest sign of rebellion.
dictionary.fusion:
Children of men...
I shall not destroy you.
Under my rule, even the most primitive of beings such as yourselves shall find a purpose.
dictionary.summon:
I am the true god among gods...
I am the Chief God who shall rule over the world!!!
Kneel before my greatness!
